config ABK_CONTROL
	bool "ABK control interface"
	help
	  Provide /dev/abk_control and a small in-kernel registration API for
	  ABK external modules that expose runtime control hooks.

	  Reading /dev/abk_control returns ABK external module metadata collected
	  at build time. Writing commands such as "disable <id>" or "enable <id>"
	  calls the matching registered control callback when one exists.
